  <!-- LOCAL KNOWLEDGE -->
  <section class="local-section" id="local">
    <h2>Chimney Sweeping in Ivanhoe</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Ivanhoe occupies the high ground above the Yarra River's lower gorge section, developed from the 1880s through the interwar period as one of Melbourne's most pleasant middle-class riverside suburbs. The suburb is characterised by Federation bungalows, Edwardian cottages and interwar brick homes on generous sloping blocks, many of which retain their original chimneys and fireplaces. The Yarra River gorge that borders Ivanhoe's western and southern edges creates a pronounced cold microclimate: cold air drains off the Templestowe plateau to the east and pools in the Yarra valley floor, and the river itself contributes moisture that makes Ivanhoe's winter mornings noticeably colder and damper than surrounding higher ground. The elevated streets along the Ivanhoe ridge can also be exposed to sharp north-westerly winds through June and July. Many Ivanhoe homes are on the market's premium side — well-maintained period properties with working fireplaces that owners use consistently through winter and maintain accordingly. We service Ivanhoe and the broader Heidelberg area regularly and are familiar with the period chimney systems and sloping-block chimney configurations common throughout the suburb.</p></div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="signs-section" id="signs">
    <h2>Signs Your Ivanhoe Chimney Needs Cleaning</h2>
    <ul class="signs-list">
      <li>Smoke coming back into the living room when you light the fire</li>
      <li>A damp or musty smell from the fireplace during wet winter weather</li>
      <li>Slow draw — the fire doesn't pull well even with the damper open</li>
      <li>Soot or dark marks above the firebox that weren't there last winter</li>
      <li>A chimney that has been used every winter but never professionally cleaned</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- SERVICES -->
  <section class="services-section" id="services">
    <h2>Chimney Services in Ivanhoe</h2>
    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Chimney Sweep</h3><p>Full brush sweep from firebox to pot. Soot, creosote and debris removed. Verbal condition report included.</p></div>
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Flue Cleaning</h3><p>Thorough flue clean using professional brushes and equipment. Removes accumulated creosote and restores full draw.</p></div>
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Wood Heater Service</h3><p>Slow combustion heater flue clean and inspection. Baffle check, door seal inspection, full flue swept top to bottom.</p></div>
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Chimney Inspection</h3><p>Visual inspection of firebox, flue, damper, crown and pot. Written report available on request. Included in the $199 service.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- REVIEWS -->
  <section class="reviews-section" id="reviews">
    <h2>What Ivanhoe Customers Say</h2>
    <div class="reviews-grid">
      <div class="review-card"><div class="review-stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div><p class="review-text">&ldquo;Federation bungalow near the Ivanhoe gorge. David swept the flue, cleared a partial blockage and gave us a full verbal report. Fireplace draws beautifully now. Will be booking every year.&rdquo;</p><p class="review-author">Philip R., Ivanhoe</p></div>
      <div class="review-card"><div class="review-stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div><p class="review-text">&ldquo;We moved in eighteen months ago and had no idea when the chimney was last cleaned. David found a significant creosote build-up and a bird nest near the pot. Very glad we called before using it.&rdquo;</p><p class="review-author">Natasha C., Ivanhoe</p></div>
      <div class="review-card"><div class="review-stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div><p class="review-text">&ldquo;Prompt, professional and very thorough. David knows his way around period chimneys. Cleaned both the firebox and the full flue and left everything spotless. Great service.&rdquo;</p><p class="review-author">Andrew M., Ivanhoe</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT -->
  <section class="about-section" id="about">
    <h2>About Dave&rsquo;s Chimney Sweeping</h2>
    <p>Dave&rsquo;s Chimney Sweeping is a local, owner-operated business covering Melbourne's inner northern suburbs including Ivanhoe. Dave personally handles every job &mdash; no subcontractors, no call centres. Flat $199 rate per chimney, no hidden fees.</p>
    <a class="btn-secondary" href="tel:0476302729">Call Dave — 0476 302 729</a>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQs -->
